title: Senators Battle Back From Pair Of Two-Goal Deficits, Lose 5-4 In Overtime vs Wild | Game Recap
creator: Locked On Senators - Daily Podcast On The Ottawa Senators
subject: Podcast
description: The Ottawa Senators were down early but they didn't give up and end up stealing a point in a 5-4 OT loss to the Minnesota Wild. Brandon Piller and Ross Levitan break down last nights game that saw Filip Gustavsson keep his team in this game, a fight from Austin Watson in his season debut and another big night for Drake Batherson. We go over what we liked from that game and some things we didn't like. The Sens finish their road trip 1-1-1 and head home for a game up against Vegas at home next!
